      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "That sounds like a truly frustrating situation, and I'm sorry you're stuck at Heathrow. To get you to Singapore as fast as possible, you'll need to look at connecting flights through major hubs with direct or very short layovers. I'd recommend checking airlines that fly to Singapore from major European hubs like Dubai (DXB), Doha (DOH), or perhaps even connecting through a major Asian hub if you can get a quick flight out of London.\n\nYou should prioritize routes with one stop, as those are usually the quickest, avoiding the multi-stop nightmare that can take days. When you check flight options, always look at the total travel time, not just the flight duration, because layover times are crucial. If you can find a route with a layover under three hours, that's usually the sweet spot for minimizing delays.\n\n*If you can provide me with the date you need to travel, I can give you more specific suggestions, but generally, look for Emirates, Qatar Airways, or Singapore Airlines connections.*\n\nGood luck with your rebooking! I hope you get moving soon.",
